Package: nimix
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Mixture Clustering and Regression with NIMBLE
Version: 1.5.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Achmad Syahrul", "Choir", email = "madsyair@stis.ac.id",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7088-0646"))
Description: Implements Bayesian mixture models and mixture regression
    using 'nimble' (de Valpine et al., 2017) <doi:10.1080/10618600.2016.1172487>.
    The package supports Binomial, Poisson, Gaussian, heavy-tailed,
    and neo-normal distributions, including the 'MSNBurr' family
    (Iriawan, 2000; Choir, 2020, ISBN:978-602-5539-45-4), together with
    distributions from the GAMLSS (Generalized Additive Models for Location,
    Scale and Shape) framework (Rigby et al., 2019)
    <doi:10.1201/9780429298547>. Four inference methods are available: finite
    mixtures, Dirichlet process mixtures, spatial Potts models, and hidden
    Markov models. Additional features include automatic prior specification,
    random effects, label-switching correction, and extensive model
    diagnostics.
